revision.text:
[[File:Abinergaos I of Charax.png|thumb|Drawing of a Coin of Abinergaos I.]][[File:Karte Charakene.png|thumb|right|Characene Kingdom.]]'''Abinergaos I''', also known as Abinerglus, was the king of [[Characene]] during the second decade of the Christian era.<ref>Monika Schuol, The Characene: A [[mesopotanian]] Kingdom in [[Hellenistic]] times. Steiner, Stuttgart 2000, page 235-236, 362-363.</ref> The years of his reign are not known beyond a few coins. The coins are dated to the years AD 10/11, 11/12, 13/14 and 22/23.<ref>''Cambridge History of Iran'', Vol. 3 (1), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Ko_RafMSGLkC&pg=PA312&lpg=PA312&dq=Abbinerigos+mentioned+by+Josephus&source=bl&ots=gHBnBTSNlk&sig=iv9q1MIvEG5dmOQ7Jc0KDs4HDT4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oHMQUZ7dBu6cmQXqm4CQDA&sqi=2&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Abbinerigos%20mentioned%20by%20Josephus&f=false page 312]</ref> However, he appears to be '''Abbinerigos''' mentioned by [[Josephus]].<ref>Josephus, Antiquities 20:2,2</ref>
