'''Anne Dufourmantelle''' (20 March 1964 – 21 July 2017) was a French philosopher and psychoanalyst.<ref name="lefigobit">{{cite news|last1=Frémont|first1=Anne-Laure|title=La philosophe Anne Dufourmantelle se noie en secourant des enfants|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/livres/2017/07/24/03005-20170724ARTFIG00036-la-philosophe-anne-dufourmantelle-se-noie-en-secourant-des-enfants.php|accessdate=24 July 2017|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=24 July 2017 |language=French }}</ref><ref name="lemondeobit">{{cite news|title=La philosophe et psychanalyste Anne Dufourmantelle se noie en secourant des enfants|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/disparitions/article/2017/07/23/la-philosophe-et-psychanalyste-anne-dufourmantelle-se-noie-en-secourant-des-enfants_5164061_3382.html|accessdate=24 July 2017|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=23 July 2017 |language=French |agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] }}</ref><ref name="libeobit">{{cite news|last1=Vécrin|first1=Anastasia|title=Mort d'Anne Dufourmantelle, philosophe et psychanalyste en liberté|url=http://www.liberation.fr/debats/2017/07/23/mort-d-anne-dufourmantelle-philosophe-et-psychanalyste-en-liberte_1585674|accessdate=24 July 2017|newspaper=[[La Libération]]|date=23 July 2017 |language=French}}</ref>

==Education and career==
Dufourmantelle was educated at [[Brown University]] and at [[Paris-Sorbonne University]], where she earned a doctorate in philosophy in 1994.<ref name=BBC>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-40703606 |title=French philosopher Dufourmantelle drowns rescuing children |publisher=[[BBC news]] |date=24 July 2017 |accessdate=25 July 2017 }}</ref> She practised [[psychoanalysis]] and was a professor at the [[European Graduate School]]<ref name=NPR>{{cite news |first=Amy |last=Held |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/07/24/539056481/french-philosopher-who-promoted-risk-taking-dies-attempting-water-rescue |title=French Philosopher Who Promoted Risk-Taking Dies Attempting Water Rescue |publisher=[[NPR]] |date=24 July 2017 |accessdate=25 July 2017 }}</ref> and a contributor to ''[[La Libération]]''.<ref name="lemondeobit"/>

Her philosophical work focused on risk taking, which she argued was essential, saying that "absolute security - like 'zero risk' - is a fantasy"<ref name=BBC/>  and that "[R]eal danger must be faced in order to survive".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gerretsen|first1=Isabelle|title=French philosopher who said 'real danger must be faced in order to survive' drowns rescuing children|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/french-philosopher-who-said-real-danger-must-be-faced-order-survive-drowns-rescuing-children-1631713|accessdate=24 July 2017|agency=World|publisher=International Business Times|date=24 July 2017}}</ref> Her book ''Éloge du risque'' or ''Praise of Risk'' was published in 2011.<ref name=BBC/>

==Death==
She died on July 21, 2017 at Pampelonne beach in Ramatuelle near the city of [[Saint-Tropez]], while trying to rescue two children caught in the Mediterranean when the water became dangerously turbulent. The children were rescued by lifeguards and survived, but Dufourmantelle could not be resuscitated.<ref name="lemondeobit"/><ref name=BBC/><ref>{{cite news|last1=O'Connor|first1=Roisin|title=Anne Dufourmantelle dead: French philosopher who wrote book on risk-taking dies rescuing children|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/news/anne-dufourmantelle-dead-mort-french-philosopher-drowned-dies-saving-children-riviera-st-tropez-a7857206.html|accessdate=24 July 2017|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=24 July 2017}}</ref>

==Honours==
Dufourmantelle won the Prix Raymond de Boyer de Sainte-Suzanne from the [[Académie française]] in 1998.<ref name=BBC/><ref name="academiefrancaiseprix">{{cite web|title=Prix Raymond de Boyer de Sainte-Suzanne|url=http://www.academie-francaise.fr/prix-raymond-de-boyer-de-sainte-suzanne|publisher=[[Académie française]]|accessdate=24 July 2017 |language=French}}</ref>

