{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=March 2017}}
'''Richard Abingdon''' (by 1491&ndash;1545), of [[Bristol]], was an English politician.

He was elected [[High Sheriff of Bristol|Sheriff of Bristol]] for 1515–16 and mayor of Bristol for 1525–26 and 1536–37. He was  constable of the staple for 1526–27 and 1543–44 and an alderman by 1538 until his death. He was elected a [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Bristol (UK Parliament constituency)|Bristol]] in 1529.

He was married to Isabel and had at least 3 sons.

